&gt; that prevents or at least ups the resistance to stun's. 

&gt; And I dare to imagine a 10th level warrior fighting two of these 
&gt; being stuned by one and then the other. And why is it so tough 
&gt; to hit them when they aren't even wearing any armor? Are thier 
&gt; skins really that much tougher than the steel in my axe? 

&gt; This agian I feel adding realism to the game wouldn't be 
&gt; disruptive. Just show some npc's with armor and some without. 
&gt; Those who aren't shown with armor shouldn't be that hard to 
&gt; kill. Those with, there should be a possibilty to salvage some 
&gt; of the armor. Agian I don't feel the economy would be that 
&gt; interupted because it would balance out. 

&gt; Since when did only players take damage from falling? It's 
&gt; because of this that surefall only makes since in PvP combat. 
&gt; Against monsters it only ensures that you don't die from the 
&gt; fall. They won't hesistate from following you. 

&gt; This is another chance for realism, what's good for the goose is 
&gt; definately good for the gander. Either cause them to take damage 
&gt; and allow that to be a valid hunting technic or cause them to 
&gt; stop at the edge. Either way would be more in tune with true 
&gt; game balance and realism. 

&gt; And since when did monsters have the perfect direction sence? 
&gt; I've had ice boned skels chase me over hills, around mountians, 
&gt; and never loose track of me. And I thought I was a good ranger. 

&gt; I agree here too, though I see the reason for this. If you could 
&gt; loose the monsters then they would have to remain hating you 
&gt; till that spawn dies. Since leaving the zone is essentially 
&gt; loosing them in a sense. This would be difficult with memory of 
&gt; mobs and with the fact that the balance of the game would still 
&gt; be tilted. 

&gt; Bows on the other hand need a complete overhall. The attack 
&gt; rates are way too slow and the damage dosn't match what it 
&gt; should. Bows were suposed to be rangers and rogues trademark 
&gt; weapons, but as they stand they only have two good uses. The 
&gt; first is to tick off monsters and get them to attack you. The 
&gt; other, the only reason I keep using a bow, is a player can pop 
&gt; one or two shots into a fleeing monster and get them back into 
&gt; melee range. I also belive the minium range idea for a bow 
&gt; stinks. I'd much perfer to see bows getting interupted rather 
&gt; than see the &quot;I'm too close even though his back is turned 
&gt; to me&quot; message. The last complaint, as with throwing 
&gt; weapons, is please allow me to pull some of what I've unloaded 
&gt; into a monster off of his corpse. 

&gt; I think I agree with every point here. Though I think arrows 
&gt; once fired are pretty much lost. Since when a wooden arrow hit's 
&gt; something it's almost guarenteed that it'll shatter. On the 
&gt; otherhand shuriken's, daggers, spears and axes should be 
&gt; recoverable. Of course they might not be found and someone else 
&gt; might pick them up, but that would be part of the game. 
